HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1183
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Officer Dresdyn Johnson
upon her receipt of the Victim Support–
Neighborhood Policing Award.
WHEREAS, our nation was conceived by individuals who were willing to sacrifice their
personal concerns to ensure the public safety and welfare, and the Volunteer State is especially
proud to be the home of so many valiant individuals who have performed above and beyond the
call of duty in service of public safety; and
WHEREAS, one such individual is Officer Dresdyn Johnson, who was recently honored
with the Chattanooga Police Department (CPD) Victim Support–Neighborhood Policing award,
in recognition of her long-standing partnership with CPD through the neighborhood policing
bureau; and
WHEREAS, Officer Johnson has exhibited the utmost dedication to supporting victims of
crimes, taking time to understand their situation while also empathizing and learning how to best
prioritize services and resources for victims and their families; and
WHEREAS, in 2025, Dresdyn Johnson truly excelled, demonstrating quick and effective
thinking by connecting an individual in crisis with specific resources and by connecting with
trauma-impacted youth at Camp Hope; and
WHEREAS, in August of that same year, she went above and beyond the call of duty
during severe flooding, placing herself in high-water situations to ensure public safety; on
Christmas Eve, Officer Johnson paid an unexpected tow bill for a visiting victim whose stolen
vehicle was recovered, ensuring the family enjoyed their holiday; and
WHEREAS, Officer Dresdyn Johnson truly embodies the department's values through
her work ethic and her ability to respond to the needs of her fellow citizens and the department;
and
HJR1183
016024
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the support provided by Officer Dresdyn Johnson has made a lasting impact
on the Chattanooga Police Department; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Officer Dresdyn Johnson upon her receipt of the
Victim Support–Neighborhood Policing award from the Chattanooga Police Department.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
